In the unconditional model, between-student variation in the initial fluency status (π0ij
) and change (π1ij
) of struggling readers (Level 2) was modeled in terms of either group mean status or group mean growth and student-level residuals while between-group variation (Level 3) in the initial fluency status and change of instructional groups was modeled as function of grand mean fluency status or grand mean fluency change and group-level residuals.
